Interface Type

All Known Subinterfaces:

public interface Type
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a generic Dimensions object type.

copyAttributes

void copyAttributes(Type sourceType)
                    throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Copies attributes defined for type sourceType into the list of attributes currently defined for this object type. The sourceType can be defined in a different product, but must be of the same object class.

Note: Only attributes that are not already defined for this object type are copied. Refresh the attribute collections after calling this method in order to see the changes.

Note: Copying attributes is not supported for user object types.

Parameters:
sourceType - a Dimensions object type whose attributes are to be copied.
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this type is a user object type.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

copyRules

void copyRules(Type sourceType)
               throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Copies attribute rules defined for type sourceType into the list of attribute rules currently defined for this object type. The sourceType can be defined in a different product, but must be of the same object class.

Note: Only rules involving attributes and lifecycle states relevant to this object type are copied.

Warning: Any update rules currently defined for this object type are deleted before the copy operation is performed.

Note: Attribute rules are not supported for user object types.

Parameters:
sourceType - a Dimensions object type whose attribute rules are to be copied.
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this type is a user object type.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

getAttributeRules

java.util.List getAttributeRules(java.lang.String attrName)

                                           boolean queryValidSetAttrs,

                                           throws DimensionsRuntimeException

Parameters:

setDisabled

void setDisabled(boolean disabled)
                 throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Sets the Disabled value for the type This flag is currently only effective in Dimensions clients with request, item and baseline types. Although the value may be stored for project/stream types and design part categories, the flag will have no effect in Dimensions clients for projects, streams and design parts.

Parameters:
disabled - the value to set
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

isDisabled

boolean isDisabled()
                   throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Gets the Disabled value for the type This flag is currently only effective in Dimensions clients with request, item and baseline types. Although the value may be stored for project/stream types and design part categories, the flag will have no effect in Dimensions clients for projects, streams and design parts.

Returns:
true/false for Disabled setting
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
